data.current_description: Queries the Chrome User Experience Report for a timeseries `history record` for a given site. Returns a `history record` that contains one or more `metric timeseries` corresponding to performance data about the requested site.
data.summary_suggestion: Query Chrome UX Report historical performance data
data.description_suggestion: Queries the Chrome User Experience Report to retrieve a timeseries history record containing real user experience metrics for a specified site. Accepts a QueryHistoryRequest with site URL and optional dimensions (form factor, effective connection type). Returns a HistoryRecord object containing one or more MetricTimeseries objects with performance data aggregated over time, including percentiles and distribution bins for metrics like First Contentful Paint, Largest Contentful Paint, and Cumulative Layout Shift.
